    "created_at": "2015-03-26T09:50:15Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-03-26T09:50:15Z",
    "body": "@alexcrichton Yes, `scan_byte` now returns `token::intern(\"?\")` instead of `token::intern(\"??\")` which is an invalid byte. I also changed some `fatal_span_` to `err_span_` in `scan_hex_digits` so the parsing can continue.\nNow it only uses `fatal_span_` when the escape sequence is not terminated (https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/23625/files#diff-d06ad31c547d2d94c8b8770006977767R749), but maybe we should read until the literal is terminated in order to continue parsing in this case? \n",
